CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 12, 1954, pg. 4, reads: "Pitt Graduation - These young men and women were among the 1561 who were granted degrees Wednesday at the spring commencement of the University of Pittsburgh. They are, left to right: Maj. Owen E. Hague, who finished degree requirements in business administration while he was one of thirty-five air force officers enrolled in a special advanced management course; Robert P. French, Master in Letters...-Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of University of Pittsburgh graduates Maj. Owen E. Hague and Robert P. "Bob" French, posed in Cathedral of Learning
